// A DEVICE doctest: `widget` declares its `Particle` shape + `Particle[4]` storage requirement in
// widget.ds.arche; its impl is behavior-only (`integrate`). The doctest below drives the device's OWN
// datasheet-declared shape — `arche test` compiles it as a generated driver over the whole device
// folder, so the datasheet's `Particle[4]` provides the pool with no manual sizing in the example.
// RUN: %arche test %s | grep -q "ok"
#import { fmt }

/// ```arche
/// main :: proc() {
///   insert(Particle, 10.0, 1.0);
///   run integrate;
///   fmt.assert(Particle.pos[0] * 10 == 110, "device doctest did not drive its shape\n");
///   fmt.printf("widget_doctest_ok\n");
/// }
/// ```
integrate :: sys (pos, vel) {
  pos = pos + vel;
}
